-- China Equity Movers: China Railway Erju, EGing, Titan Wind
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2012-07-31T07:43:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-31/china-equity-movers-china-railway-erju-eging-titan-wind.html
China ’s Shanghai Composite Index,
which tracks the bigger of China’s stock exchanges, falls 0.3%,
capping 5.5% decline this month. CSI 300 Index drops 0.1%.  ADVANCERS:
* China Railway Erju (600528 CH) +3%; Gem-Year Industrial
(601002 CH) +3.3%; Chinese cities may spend at least 1 tln  yuan 
building subways from 2010-2015, China Daily reports  DECLINERS:
* EGing Photovoltaic Technology (600537 CH) -2.5%, lowest close
since September 2009; Zhejiang Sunflower (300111 CH) -4.9%,
lowest close on record; Trina Solar (TSL US) lowers estimate of
2Q solar module shipments by as much as 25%
* Yunnan Aluminium (000807 CH) -3.5%; Co. to absorb Yunnan
Wansheng Carbon, exchange statement says
* Titan Wind Energy (002531 CH) -10% daily limit; U.S. Commerce
Department set 20.85% preliminary anti-dumping duty on wind-
tower imports from Co.  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
